# Copy this file to ".env" (gitignored) and fill in your real keys.
# Restart "npm run dev" after editing.

# ── Real AI photo-diagnosis (module "Analyse IA") — pick ONE of the two setups below ──

# Option A (recommended for any deployed/shared app — SECURE):
# Deploy supabase/functions/analyse-plante, set its OPENAI_API_KEY secret server-side,
# then point the app at it. The OpenAI key never reaches the browser.
# VITE_PLANT_VISION_ENDPOINT=https://<project-ref>.supabase.co/functions/v1/analyse-plante
# VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=

# ── Premium subscriptions (4,99€/mois) via Google Play Billing + RevenueCat ──
# Only meaningful inside the native Android app shell (see /android, Capacitor).
# Public/SDK key from the RevenueCat dashboard (Project settings > API keys > Public app-specific key for Google Play).
# VITE_REVENUECAT_PUBLIC_SDK_KEY=goog_...
# (Server-side) supabase/functions/revenuecat-webhook syncs entitlement changes
# into the `subscriptions` table — configure REVENUECAT_WEBHOOK_AUTH_TOKEN as a
# Supabase secret and set the same value as the Authorization header in the
# RevenueCat dashboard webhook settings.

# Option B (quick personal/local setup — key is visible in browser network requests):
# Get a key at https://platform.openai.com/api-keys — it must have access
# to a vision-capable chat model (gpt-4o-mini works well and is inexpensive).
VITE_OPENAI_API_KEY=

# Optional — override the default vision model (default: gpt-4o-mini)
# VITE_OPENAI_VISION_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini

# Optional — existing remote assistant endpoint used by "Assistant potager"
# VITE_ASSISTANT_ENDPOINT=
